	doi = {10.23919/EuCAP51087.2021.9411331},
	abstract = {3D printed objects are usually not completely filled to reduce weight, printing time and costs. Instead, infill structures are used. These infill structures have a major influence on the strength of 3D prints. To non-destructively investigate such infill structures, our approach is the use of terahertz time-domain spectroscopy. This paper studies possible evaluation parameters for imaging an exemplary infill structure by using both transmission and reflection measurements. Thus, a non-destructive visualization of 3D print infill structures is enabled.},
